    },
    {
      "id": "CyZlI22bSjc3bvl5AZpJd",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 13607.917397673147,
      "y": -584.5635721755849,
      "width": 756.35888671875,
      "height": 250,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b05",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1075053436,
      "version": 484,
      "versionNonce": 706493180,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1779791906508,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1. How do we ensure our cache is highly available and fault tolerant?\n   ❌ Synchronous replication \n      - strong consistency guarantees\n      - write operations must wait for confirmation from all replicas before completing\n   ✅ Asynchronous replication\n      - eventual consistency model\n      - complex conflict resolution\n      - need a mechanism to promote one of the replicas to become the new primary\n   ✅✅ Peer-to-peer replication \n      - gossip protocol ensures that changes eventually reach all nodes in the cluster",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1. How do we ensure our cache is highly available and fault tolerant?\n   ❌ Synchronous replication \n      - strong consistency guarantees\n      - write operations must wait for confirmation from all replicas before completing\n   ✅ Asynchronous replication\n      - eventual consistency model\n      - complex conflict resolution\n      - need a mechanism to promote one of the replicas to become the new primary\n   ✅✅ Peer-to-peer replication \n      - gossip protocol ensures that changes eventually reach all nodes in the cluster",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "r5PaBY0wOSj3xE4jAwnun",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 16095.327035526627,
      "y": -3.022164265595734,
      "width": 568.75927734375,
      "height": 125,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b06",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1286540484,
      "version": 921,
      "versionNonce": 2091955652,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1779791892223,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Estimate the number of nodes:\n    - single host be able to perform 20,000 requests per second \n    - we would need at least 100,000 / 20,000 \n    - 5 nodes to handle our throughput requirements\n    - ~10 nodes to handle peek",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Estimate the number of nodes:\n    - single host be able to perform 20,000 requests per second \n    - we would need at least 100,000 / 20,000 \n    - 5 nodes to handle our throughput requirements\n    - ~10 nodes to handle peek",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "Nb-Ql-GzXVsLwrjGCY8JD",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 16096.272191538148,
      "y": 176.92098657012832,
      "width": 427.259521484375,
      "height": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b07",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1251157244,
      "version": 934,
      "versionNonce": 1018001660,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1779791926774,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Storage requirements:\n    -  typical instance with 24GB RAM \n    - 1024GB / 24GB = 43 nodes just for storage\n    - ~50 nodes with buffer",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Storage requirements:\n    -  typical instance with 24GB RAM \n    - 1024GB / 24GB = 43 nodes just for storage\n    - ~50 nodes with buffer",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "Bh_hvXYOC9lKfoPp8BA5l",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 13613.15156955521,
      "y": -226.56608201073414,
      "width": 950.2386474609375,
      "height": 150,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b08",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 120935036,
      "version": 471,
      "versionNonce": 89357180,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1779791906508,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "2. How can we ensure an even distribution of keys across our nodes?\n    ❌ Modulo operation\n        - this works great when you have a fixed number of nodes\n    ✅ Consistent hashing\n        - if a node is added or removed, only the keys that fall within that node's range need to be remapped\n        - rather than having to redistribute all keys across all nodes",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "2. How can we ensure an even distribution of keys across our nodes?\n    ❌ Modulo operation\n        - this works great when you have a fixed number of nodes\n    ✅ Consistent hashing\n        - if a node is added or removed, only the keys that fall within that node's range need to be remapped\n        - rather than having to redistribute all keys across all nodes",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "mCDzGTZpAEJW-z_srV390",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 14595.987837704406,
      "y": -589.2679464087602,
      "width": 1019.618408203125,
      "height": 475,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b09",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 668071164,
      "version": 642,
      "versionNonce": 1758374908,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1779791906508,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "3. What happens if you have a hot key that is being read from a lot?\n    ❌ Vertical scaling all nodes\n        -  expensive and inefficient solution \n        - since we're upgrading resources for all nodes when only some are experiencing high load\n    ✅ Dedicated Hot key cache\n        - creating a separate caching layer specifically for handling hot keys\n        - managing consistency between the main cache and hot key cache adds complexity.\n    ✅ Read replicas\n        - significant overhead of storage and network bandwidth \n    ✅✅ Copies of hot keys\n        - system creates multiple copies of hot keys across different nodes to distribute read load\n        - first, system monitors key to detect hot keys that are frequently read\n        - when a key becomes \"hot\", instead of having just one copy as user:123, the system creates multiple copies:\n                - user:123#1 -> Node A stores a copy\n                - user:123#2 -> Node B stores a copy\n                - user:123#3 -> Node C stores a copy\n        - these copies get distributed to different nodes via consistent hashing\n        - for reads, clients randomly choose one of the suffixed keys\n        - for writes, the system must update all copies to maintain consistency",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "3. What happens if you have a hot key that is being read from a lot?\n    ❌ Vertical scaling all nodes\n        -  expensive and inefficient solution \n        - since we're upgrading resources for all nodes when only some are experiencing high load\n    ✅ Dedicated Hot key cache\n        - creating a separate caching layer specifically for handling hot keys\n        - managing consistency between the main cache and hot key cache adds complexity.\n    ✅ Read replicas\n        - significant overhead of storage and network bandwidth \n    ✅✅ Copies of hot keys\n        - system creates multiple copies of hot keys across different nodes to distribute read load\n        - first, system monitors key to detect hot keys that are frequently read\n        - when a key becomes \"hot\", instead of having just one copy as user:123, the system creates multiple copies:\n                - user:123#1 -> Node A stores a copy\n                - user:123#2 -> Node B stores a copy\n                - user:123#3 -> Node C stores a copy\n        - these copies get distributed to different nodes via consistent hashing\n        - for reads, clients randomly choose one of the suffixed keys\n        - for writes, the system must update all copies to maintain consistency",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "kBIqzkGQsEDktR_e1ki4l",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 15700.581282697429,
      "y": -557.0442335300594,
      "width": 953.5386962890625,
      "height": 350,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0A",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 291335236,
      "version": 322,
      "versionNonce": 110087292,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1779791906508,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "4. What happens if you have a hot key that is being written to a lot?\n    ✅✅ Write batching\n            - collecting multiple write operations over a short time window \n            - and applying them as a single atomic update\n            - this reduces the write pressure on the cache node \n            - trade-off is a small delay in write visibility\n    ✅✅ Sharding hot keys with suffix\n            - a hot counter key \"views:video123\" might be split into 10 shards\n                    - \"views:video123:1\"\n                    - ........\n                    -  \"views:video123:10\"\n            - when a write arrives, the system randomly selects one of these shards to update.\n            - increased complexity of read operations, which now need to aggregate data from multiple shards\n            - the challenge of maintaining consistency across shards",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "4. What happens if you have a hot key that is being written to a lot?\n    ✅✅ Write batching\n            - collecting multiple write operations over a short time window \n            - and applying them as a single atomic update\n            - this reduces the write pressure on the cache node \n            - trade-off is a small delay in write visibility\n    ✅✅ Sharding hot keys with suffix\n            - a hot counter key \"views:video123\" might be split into 10 shards\n                    - \"views:video123:1\"\n                    - ........\n                    -  \"views:video123:10\"\n            - when a write arrives, the system randomly selects one of these shards to update.\n            - increased complexity of read operations, which now need to aggregate data from multiple shards\n            - the challenge of maintaining consistency across shards",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
